{"TopicId":178470,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"LGPLv3 and old mod re-use","CreatedByName":"Tyko","CreatedById":164179,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-09-22T13:08:02Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Tyko","CreatedById":164179,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-09-22T13:08:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAm I allowed to reuse parts and configs from an old mod that were published under LGPLv3? I\u0027ve been reading over the info on \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.gnu.org/licenses/lgpl-3.0.en.html\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ethe LGPL website\u003C/a\u003E and can\u0027t figure out how it would apply since there are no libraries or application.\u00A0 If I can reuse them, besides the \u0022not selling it\u0022 part, what other limitations am I under?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/129964-linuxgurugamer/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022129964\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/129964-linuxgurugamer/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@linuxgurugamer\u003C/a\u003E, I know you\u0027ve become an expert at re-use, hoping you can weigh in?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks all!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-09-22T13:08:33Z\u0022 title=\u002209/22/2018 01:08  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 22, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Tyko\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-09-22T13:20:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nyes, but they will continue to be under the LGPL, be sure to be specific in your licensing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr,, just have your new mod under the LGPL.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}